<item>
            <title>[LU-12084] Interop: sanity test 256 fails with &#8220;Empty plain llog was not deleted from changelog catalog&#8221;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12084</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity test_256 fails in interop testing with &apos;Empty plain llog was not deleted from changelog catalog&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7443&quot; title=&quot;cancel record doesn`t delete empty plain llog&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7443&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7443&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/17227&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/17227&lt;/a&gt;, we see that sanity test 256 was added to Lustre version 2.7.90. Thus, it&#8217;s clear that we need to add a Lustre version check for this test and not run this test for all interop testing with servers with version less than 2.7.90.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
